// Characteresticts of Lambda Expression

1. If body has only one function we can remove curly brackets

// Example

(int a, int b) -> {
  System.out.println(a+b);
}

(int a, int b) -> System.out.println(a + b);

2. Use type interface means compiler will automatically guess the situation and context

// Example

(a,b) -> System.out.println(a + b);

3. No return Keyword

  // Example
  (str) -> str.length();

4. If we have only one parameter then remove bracket

str -> str.length();
